orne are the main philosophical resources. As it maintains the significance of theistic metaphysics, the book makes no appeal to religious authority but solely to common human experience, and on this basis articulates principles of human purpose and democratic justice.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aDemocracy -- Philosophy. 0aDemocracy -- Religious aspects. 0aDemocracyxPhilosophy. 0aDemocracyxReligious aspects. 0aEthics. 0aFirst philosophy. 0aMetaphysics. 0aReligion and ethics. 0aTheism. 4aPhilosophy : Metaphysics. 4aPhilosophy : Philosophy of Religion. 4aPhilosophy : Philosophy. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Religion. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Metaphysics.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143843594740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438435947423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438435947/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles